  "title": "Is the European Union Worth It Or Should We End It?",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 540.0,
      "end_time": 3280.0,
      "text": "Do you think the European Union is worth it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3280.0,
      "end_time": 6120.0,
      "text": "Or, should we end it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6120.0,
      "end_time": 11940.0,
      "text": "Many people feel a strong disconnect with the EU, while others praise its achievements."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11940.0,
      "end_time": 27360.0,
      "text": "Everything considered: Is its existence good or bad for Europeans?"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27360.0,
      "end_time": 33560.0,
      "text": "Since it looks like the UK is leaving the EU, we&#39;ll mostly treat it as if it&#39;s no longer part of the club."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 33560.0,
      "end_time": 40420.0,
      "text": "The European Union, combining its 27 member countries, has a population of about 450 million people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 40420.0,
      "end_time": 44520.0,
      "text": "making it the third most populous sort-of country in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 44520.0,
      "end_time": 51160.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the world&#39;s second largest economy by GDP, and has the biggest single market in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 51160.0,
      "end_time": 57660.0,
      "text": "But originally, the creation of the European Union was all about one thing: Peace."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 57660.0,
      "end_time": 59600.0,
      "text": "Europeans are really good at war,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 59600.0,
      "end_time": 64220.0,
      "text": "so they were involved in bloody conflicts for basically all their history."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 64220.0,
      "end_time": 66720.0,
      "text": "A century-long rivalry between Germany and France"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 66720.0,
      "end_time": 69740.0,
      "text": "alone, cost millions of lives and ran so deeply"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 69740.0,
      "end_time": 72680.0,
      "text": "that Germans invented their own word for it:"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 72680.0,
      "end_time": 75080.0,
      "text": "Erbfeindschaft."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 75080.0,
      "end_time": 77760.0,
      "text": "After the second World War, Europeans decided"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 77760.0,
      "end_time": 80040.0,
      "text": "they wanted lasting peace that was not"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 80040.0,
      "end_time": 82160.0,
      "text": "based on a balance of military power."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 82160.0,
      "end_time": 85740.0,
      "text": "Instead, the economies, politics, and peoples of Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 85740.0,
      "end_time": 88640.0,
      "text": "should become so closely interconnected, that war"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 88640.0,
      "end_time": 92200.0,
      "text": "would become both impractical and unthinkable."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 92200.0,
      "end_time": 93800.0,
      "text": "The plan worked!"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 93800.0,
      "end_time": 98800.0,
      "text": "Between EU members, we&#39;ve had over 70 years of peace."
